', 'Python-dotenv reads key-value pairs from a ', ' file and can set them as environment
variables. It helps in the development of applications following the
', ' principles.', 'If your application takes its configuration from environment variables, like a 12-factor
application, launching it in development is not very practical because you have to set
those environment variables yourself.', 'To help you with that, you can add Python-dotenv to your application to make it load the
configuration from a ', ' file when it is present (e.g. in development) while remaining
configurable via the environment:', 'By default, ', " doesn't override existing environment variables.", 'To configure the development environment, add a ', ' in the root directory of your
project:', 'The syntax of ', ' files supported by python-dotenv is similar to that of Bash:', 'If you use variables in values, ensure they are surrounded with ', ' and ', ', like
', ', as bare variables such as ', ' are not expanded.', 'You will probably want to add ', ' to your ', ', especially if it contains
secrets like a password.', 'See the section "File format" below for more information about what you can write in a
', ' file.', 'The function ', ' works more or less the same way as ', ", except it
doesn't touch the environment, it just returns a ", ' with the values parsed from the
', ' file.', 'This notably enables advanced configuration management:', ' and ', ' accept ', ' via their ', '
argument.  It is thus possible to load the variables from sources other than the
filesystem (e.g. the network).', 'You can use dotenv in IPython.  By default, it will use ', ' to search for a
', ' file:', 'You can also specify a path:', 'Optional flags:', 'A CLI interface ', ' is also included, which helps you manipulate the ', ' file
without manually opening it.', 'Run ', ' for more information about the options and subcommands.', 'The format is not formally specified and still improves over time.  That being said,
', ' files should mostly look like Bash files.', 'Keys can be unquoted or single-quoted. Values can be unquoted, single- or double-quoted.
Spaces before and after keys, equal signs, and values are ignored. Values can be followed
by a comment.  Lines can start with the ', ' directive, which does not affect their
interpretation.', 'Allowed escape sequences:', 'It is possible for single- or double-quoted values to span multiple lines.  The following
examples are equivalent:', 'A variable can have no value:', 'It results in ', ' associating that variable name with the value ', ' (e.g.
', '. ', ', on the other hand, simply ignores such variables.', "This shouldn't be confused with ", ', in which case the variable is associated with the
empty string.', 'Python-dotenv can interpolate variables using POSIX variable expansion.', 'With ', ' or ', ', the value of a variable is the
first of the values defined in the following list:', 'With ', ', the value of a variable is the first of the values
defined in the following list:', 'This project is currently maintained by ', ' and
', ' and would not have been possible
without the support of these ', '.', '
